{{Infobox language |name=Alemán Coloniero |states=[[Venezuela]] |speakers=1,500 |date=2009 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Indo-European |fam2=[[Germanic languages|Germanic]] |fam3=[[West Germanic languages|West Germanic]] |fam4=[[High German languages|High German]] |fam5=[[Upper German]] |fam6=[[Alemannic German|Alemannic]] |fam7=[[Low Alemannic German|Low Alemannic]] |iso3=gct |glotto=colo1254 |glottorefname=Colonia Tovar German }} The '''Colonia Tovar dialect''', or Alemán Coloniero, is a dialect spoken in '''[[Colonia Tovar]]''', [[Venezuela]], that belongs to the [[Low Alemannic German|Low Alemannic]] branch of [[German language|German]].
==Characteristics==
The dialect, like other [[Alemannic German|Alemannic dialects]], is not mutually intelligible with [[Standard German]]. It is spoken by descendants of Germans from the [[Black Forest]] region of southern [[Baden]], who emigrated to Venezuela in 1843. Most speakers also speak [[Spanish language|Spanish]], and the language has also acquired some Spanish [[loanword]]s.
==Literature== *Blanco Hernández, Marlene: ''{{lang|es|Introducción al analisis gramatical del Aleman de la Colonia Tovar.}}'' Universidad Central de Venezuela. Caracas 1987. *Redlich Perkins, Renate: ''Tovar German. Linguistic study of a German century alemannic dialect spoken in Venezuela.'' University Microfilms International. Ann Arbor, Michigan, London 1978. *Da Rin, Denise: ''{{lang|de|Die deutsche Sprache in der Colonia Tovar (Venezuela) - Eine soziolinguistische Untersuchung.}}'' München 1995. * Kanzler, Samuel Briceño: ''{{lang|es|La Colonia Tovar y su gente.}}'' Tovar, o. J. (Title in German translation: ''{{lang|de|Die Colonia Tovar und ihre Menschen}}'').
