s The Penguin, from the Batman comic books. * [[Gentleman Ghost|Jim Craddock]], also known as Gentleman Ghost, from the DC Comics universe. * [[Gambit (comics)|Remy Etienne LeBeau]], also known as Gambit, from the X-Men comics. * [[Black Cat (Marvel Comics)|Felicia Hardy]], also known as Black Cat, from the Spider-Man comics. * [[Maurice Leblanc]]'s [[Arsène Lupin]] * Viper and also Valmont from the animated [[Jackie Chan Adventures]]. * Thomas Hewett Edward Cat from the TV series [[T.H.E. Cat]]. * [[Danny Ocean (character)|Danny Ocean]] from ''[[Ocean's 11]]'' and the ''[[Ocean's Trilogy]]'' of films. * Captain Feeney in ''[[Barry Lyndon]]'' * David Goldman in ''[[An Education]]''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newyorker.com/arts/reviews/film/an_education_scherfig|title=An Education|work=The New Yorker|last=Denby|first=David|date=28 October 2009}}</ref> * Sir Charles Litton, also known as "The Phantom" in ''[[The Pink Panther (1963 film)|The Pink Panther]]'' * [[Sly Cooper (character)|Sly Cooper]] from the [[Sly Cooper|franchise of the same name]]. * [[Characters of the Mass Effect universe#Kasumi Goto|Kasumi Goto]] from the ''[[Mass Effect]]'' video game series. Her name approximately translates to "phantom thief." * [[Flambeau (character)|M. Hercule Flambeau]] from the [[Father Brown]] short stories by [[G. K. Chesterton]]. * Sir Oliver from the [[Alan Ford (comics)|Alan Ford]] comics. * [[Flynn Rider]] in ''[[Tangled]]'' * Locke Lamora from Scott Lynch's ''[[The Gentleman Bastard Sequence]]''. * Lady Christina de Souza from the Dr. Who Episode "[[Planet of the Dead]]". * Moist von Lipwig from [[Terry Pratchett]]'s [[Discworld]] novels; he is the main character of ''Going Postal'', ''Making Money'', and ''Raising Steam''. * Sophie Deveraux, former lady thief turned vigilante, from [[Leverage (TV series)]]. * Chance Sequoyah<ref>{{cite weburl=http://thepenumbrapodcast.wikia.com/wiki/The_Coyote_of_the_Painted_Plains}}</ref>, bandit and foster parent to orphaned chil